mall cramped room in the Temple of Solusek Ro, and she longed for the hot, dank air of the temple with a deep sigh. <br>
<br>
         The Gnome stammered with his response, “Wuh-wuh-wuh-well M’lady the arrangements have been made for your entrance to the city. Your companions are standing nearby, awaiting your order. Your plans for escape are in place as well.” The Gnome, visibly trembling under the heavy gaze of the Tier’Dal, breathed a sigh of relief as Vdou solemnly nodded and turned towards the door. Hoblenoop Bremblebar fell against the wall with a heavy sigh, his small frame seemed ever smaller in the deep black of the room and he began to weep…<br>
<br>
<br>
         The explosions came as quite a surprise to the Guards just inside the gates of Felwithe their frail bodies barely able to withstand the powerful force of the blast. “To arms! We are besieged!” cried the helpless Paladins, but to no avail. Vdou and her Tier’Dal companions had already slipped in through the confusion and slit their throats, their cries now nothing more but forced gurgling. The valiant Koada’Dal surged to the sound of the explosion and met the Tier’Dal head on, the sounds of battle echoing through the gleaming white passages of Felwithe. Matched one to one, the ensuing battle played out quite evenly, much to the Tier’Dal’s surprise. The Tier’Dal had an advantage in the battle though, they were the only ones that knew the purpose of their visit; they were only there for but a moment, and only served as a distraction for the Sorceress’ scheme.<br>
<br>
         Vdou entered Felwithe with a wide grin on her face, knowing that her plan had come together with flawless perfection. The brave guards of Felwithe nearly fell over as they saw what happened next. Vdou had begun an incantation, wildly twisting her arms and fingers about her body all the while chanting in a tongue so foreign it made the Koada’Dal cower in fear. The sky turned black, and a howling screech sounded from above, suddenly a giant ball of ice streaked down from the heavens landing on three of the guards, plowing them ten feet underground with a sickening splat. The Tier’Dal pulled an object from under her robe, perfectly round and surrounded by a dull black glow. Vdou threw the sphere into the air and shouted an incantation, immediately the orb flashed brightly and all was quiet. <br>
<br>
         Time had stood still. <br>
<br>
         Vdou made her way past the frozen soldiers, across the bridge and down to the Guild Hall of the Clerics of Tunare. All stood motionless in the town, save for the Dark Elf whose long flowing robe gingerly clung to her svelte form while she walked silently towards the door of the Temple…<br>
